abstract: William C Rhoden Sports of The Times column on franchise popularity of New York Giants and New York Jets; says that the Jets, with coach Rex Ryan, are finally on par with the Giants, but team needs to continue to win games to stay in spotlight.
snippet: Over the previous two seasons, the Jets, with Rex Ryan, have cut into the Giants’ traditional stranglehold on buzz, news media exposure and public preference.
lead_paragraph: Over the previous two seasons, the Jets, with Rex Ryan, have cut into the Giants’ traditional stranglehold on buzz, news media exposure and public preference.

headline.main: Giants Still Own City’s Hearts, but Jets Are Closing in Fast

headline.seo: Jets Gaining Ground on Giants in Battle for the City
